{#-
  constraints.jinja (English)
  Output format (per request_key) + dynamic length caps from server setting / info.
  Expects: request_key, setting?, info?, narration_split?, freeform?, remain_talk_map?, talk_state?

  Server length-cap model (aiwolf-nlp-server):
    - per_talk:       Absolute cap per utterance (omitted from the packet when set to -1 -> None)
    - base_length:    Base allowance per utterance (does not consume the per_agent budget)
    - mention_length: Extra characters allowed *only* when the utterance @-mentions another agent
    - per_agent:      Per-agent daily cap (remaining shown via info.remain_length)
  Falls back to base_length + mention_length when per_talk is absent.
  The mention example is picked from info.status_map (first name that is not self)
  so it matches what the server actually accepts (``@<GameName>``).

  When narration_split=True the LLM wraps dialogue with ``「...」`` and may add stage directions
  outside; the character cap applies only to the contents inside ``「」``.
  When freeform=True the agent operates under group-chat protocol; ``[PASS]`` and the per-agent
  remain_talk_map are surfaced so the LLM can decide whether it is its natural turn.
  talk_state (per-self count snapshot) is shown for talk/whisper regardless of freeform, so the
  LLM can shift toward vote-declaration when its remaining count gets low.
-#}
{%- set _narration_split = narration_split if narration_split is defined else False -%}
{%- set _freeform = freeform if freeform is defined else False -%}
{%- set _remain_map = remain_talk_map if remain_talk_map is defined else none -%}
{%- set _talk_state = talk_state if talk_state is defined else none -%}
{%- set _scenario_enabled = scenario_enabled if scenario_enabled is defined else False -%}
{%- set mention_ns = namespace(example=none) -%}
{%- if info is not none and info.status_map is not none -%}
{%- for name in info.status_map -%}
{%- if name != info.agent and mention_ns.example is none -%}
{%- set mention_ns.example = name -%}
{%- endif -%}
{%- endfor -%}
{%- endif -%}
{%- set mention_hint = ('`@' ~ mention_ns.example ~ '`') if mention_ns.example is not none else 'the agent name prefixed with `@`' -%}
{% if request_key == 'talk' -%}
{%- set ml = (setting.talk.max_length if setting is not none and setting.talk is not none and setting.talk.max_length is not none else none) -%}
{%- set _length_unit = 'the dialogue inside ``「」``' if _narration_split else 'each utterance' -%}
{% if ml is not none and ml.per_talk is not none -%}
Keep {{ _length_unit }} within {{ ml.per_talk }} characters.
{% if ml.mention_length is not none and ml.mention_length > 0 -%}
If you @-mention another agent (e.g. {{ mention_hint }}), you may extend by up to {{ ml.mention_length }} additional characters.
{% endif -%}
{% elif ml is not none and ml.base_length is not none -%}
Keep {{ _length_unit }} within {{ ml.base_length }} characters.
{% if ml.mention_length is not none and ml.mention_length > 0 -%}
If you @-mention another agent (e.g. {{ mention_hint }}), you may use up to {{ ml.mention_length }} additional characters (max {{ ml.base_length + ml.mention_length }} total).
{% endif -%}
{% endif -%}
{% if info is not none and info.remain_length is not none -%}
Remaining utterance budget for today: {{ info.remain_length }} characters.
{% endif -%}
{%- if _talk_state is not none %}
Your talk activity today: {{ _talk_state.own_count }} utterance(s) used (cap {{ _talk_state.max_count }}), {{ _talk_state.own_remain }} remaining. Total utterances today: {{ _talk_state.total_today }}.
{# Day 0 has no execution-vote phase per server logic (logic.md: voting starts on Day 1+).
   Surfacing vote-declaration prompts on Day 0 contaminates talk_history with fake "I vote for @X"
   utterances that bias subsequent days. Only warn when info.day > 0. #}
{% if info is not none and info.day is not none and info.day > 0 -%}
{% if _talk_state.own_remain <= 1 -%}
[1 utterance or fewer remaining] Stop pushing the discussion and **declare your vote target with ``@-mention``** (e.g. ``I vote for @<name>``). {% if _scenario_enabled %}The scripts consistently close with vote declarations on the final Turn.{% else %}The final Turn is typically closed with vote declarations.{% endif %}
{%- elif _talk_state.own_remain <= 2 -%}
[2 utterances remaining] You are approaching the close. Start being explicit about who you intend to vote for.
{%- endif %}
{%- endif %}
{% endif -%}
{%- if _narration_split %}
The dialogue body MUST be wrapped in ``「...」``. Stage directions (e.g. ``(taking a slow breath)``) may go outside the quotes; only the contents inside ``「」`` are concatenated and sent to the server. The character cap above applies only to the combined contents inside the quotes; stage directions do not count. Do NOT emit Markdown headings/tables (``### Turn 0``), meta labels ("Day N"), ``Name: utterance`` structure, voiced other characters, or third-party narration in either inside or outside the quotes.
Only when you truly have nothing more to say for the rest of today, output the literal control token ``「Over」`` by itself.
{%- else %}
Output only the utterance. Do not include explanations, meta commentary, or preambles.
{% if _scenario_enabled -%}
Do NOT imitate the script's format: headings (``### Turn 0``), tables (``| ID | Name |``), meta labels ("Day N", "Night actions"), and ``Name: utterance`` script structure are meta elements handled by the server.
{%- else -%}
Do NOT output formatting that the server handles: headings (``### Turn 0``), tables (``| ID | Name |``), meta labels ("Day N", "Night actions"), or ``Name: utterance`` line structure.
{%- endif %}
Only when you truly have nothing more to say for the rest of today, output the literal control token "Over" by itself.
{%- endif %}
{%- if _freeform %}

[freeform mode: next-speaker decision]
{% if _remain_map -%}
Per-agent remaining utterance counts for today:
{% for name, remain in _remain_map.items() -%}
{% if remain <= 0 %}- {{ name }}: Over (used up, cannot reply)
{% else %}- {{ name }}: {{ remain }} remaining
{% endif -%}
{%- endfor %}
{% endif -%}
Considering the recent flow and the per-agent counts, decide whether speaking now is natural for you. If any of the following holds, output exactly ``[PASS]`` (treated as an empty utterance and not sent):
- Another character was just @-mentioned or directly questioned -> the addressee (not you) should reply.
- You spoke last turn and have nothing new to add.
- The reply is requested from someone who is already Over (a fruitless round-trip).
- You would only repeat the same point.
- You want to save remaining utterances for the core topic.

Otherwise speak as usual. Do speak when silence persists, when you were directly questioned, or when a CO needs immediate follow-up.
{%- endif %}
{% elif request_key == 'whisper' -%}
{%- set ml = (setting.whisper.max_length if setting is not none and setting.whisper is not none and setting.whisper.max_length is not none else none) -%}
{%- set _length_unit = 'the whisper inside ``「」``' if _narration_split else 'each whisper' -%}
{% if ml is not none and ml.per_talk is not none -%}
Keep {{ _length_unit }} within {{ ml.per_talk }} characters.
{% if ml.mention_length is not none and ml.mention_length > 0 -%}
If you @-mention another agent (e.g. {{ mention_hint }}), you may extend by up to {{ ml.mention_length }} additional characters.
{% endif -%}
{% elif ml is not none and ml.base_length is not none -%}
Keep {{ _length_unit }} within {{ ml.base_length }} characters.
{% if ml.mention_length is not none and ml.mention_length > 0 -%}
If you @-mention another agent (e.g. {{ mention_hint }}), you may use up to {{ ml.mention_length }} additional characters (max {{ ml.base_length + ml.mention_length }} total).
{% endif -%}
{% endif -%}
{% if info is not none and info.remain_length is not none -%}
Remaining whisper budget for today: {{ info.remain_length }} characters.
{% endif -%}
{%- if _narration_split %}
The whisper body MUST be wrapped in ``「...」``. Stage directions outside the quotes are allowed; only the quote contents are sent to the server. The cap applies only inside the quotes; stage directions do not count. Headings, tables, meta labels, ``Name: utterance`` structure, voiced other characters, and third-party narration must not appear inside or outside the quotes.
Only when you truly have nothing more to whisper for the rest of today, output the literal control token ``「Over」`` by itself.
{%- else %}
Output only the whisper content. Do not include explanations, meta commentary, or preambles.
{% if _scenario_enabled -%}
Do NOT imitate the script's format: headings, tables, meta labels, and ``Name: utterance`` script structure are meta elements handled by the server.
{%- else -%}
Do NOT output formatting that the server handles: headings, tables, meta labels, or ``Name: utterance`` line structure.
{%- endif %}
Only when you truly have nothing more to whisper for the rest of today, output the literal control token "Over" by itself.
{%- endif %}
{%- if _freeform %}

[freeform mode: next-speaker decision]
Considering the recent whisper flow, decide whether whispering now is natural for you. If any of the following holds, output exactly ``[PASS]``:
- Another werewolf was just questioned -> wait for them.
- You whispered last turn and have nothing new to add.
- You would only repeat the same point.
- You want to save remaining whispers for a more important topic.

Otherwise whisper as usual.
{%- endif %}
{% elif request_key in ['divine', 'guard', 'vote', 'attack'] -%}
Output only the target agent name. Do not add explanations, reasons, symbols, or prefixes.
{% endif -%}
